caption: b'When we asked our customers to share their thanks for those who put food on their tables, they delivered. We got hundreds of messages and\xc2\xa0handwritten notes expressing two words that aren\xe2\x80\x99t said nearly enough: Thank You.:red_heart_selector:'

b'Veterans, we thank you.'

b"In the latest episode of the Something Greater podcast, we're looking at recruiting talent in small-town businesses.  But our focus isn't just on the job, it's on what that job can mean to the community.  Tune into Something Greater via the link in our bio or anywhere you listen to podcasts."

b':megaphone: Calling all grad students! :megaphone: Are you looking to line up a summer internship in corporate strategy? b'Our dairy and ag members are always working hard to feed the country \xe2\x80\x94\xc2\xa0in more ways than one. Check out their story in this video from their work in 2019!\n.\nOctober is National Co-Op Month and we have been highlighting stories featuring our co-op owners. Learn more at the link in our bio.'

b':red_heart: this story from @farmweeknow: When an Illinois principal had an unconventional idea to safely store school supplies, Purina came through with a good old-fashioned fix that was more than just a drop in the bucket. Principal Stark, whose kids show pigs, remembered the large buckets his family uses for feed. He reached out to Purina to see about using those containers for the classroom. Turns out, they were the perfect size and shape for his students\xe2\x80\x99 needs! 600 buckets later, these unique storage solutions get a gold star from teachers.:white_medium_star:'

b'Our co-op members are integral members & builders of their community. b'Farmers. Entrepreneurs. Innovators. Like many of the members who make up our co-op, Ed & Deb Staats have generated extra income by getting creative with the trees on their farm. b'Today is #NationalFarmersDay. Join us in cheering extra loud to acknowledge the grit, resilience and never-ending hard work of the farmers who never gave up on feeding the world during this difficult year. America\xe2\x80\x99s farmers who are using cutting-edge technology to feed the world even though 2020 challenges every facet of our daily lives. Those who grow our food have never slowed down, and for that, we express our deepest thanks.
.
However, we also must recognize that #agtech isn\xe2\x80\x99t accessible to 1 in 4 farmers \xe2\x80\x93 hindering food security and the rural quality of life. That\xe2\x80\x99s why we\xe2\x80\x99re taking action to close the digital divide, by rallying partners to make free Wi-Fi available across the country. 

More details in our bio link.'

b'Do you share our passion for animals? Visit the link in our bio. \n.\n#FeedingTheProgress2020 #FeedingHumanProgress'

b'#InternationalWomensDay is this weekend. Did you know that women make up >40% of the global ag workforce, but receive only a fraction of the land and training as their male counterparts?
